UPDATE sys_function SET descript = 'It allows to repair the problem of having two nodes on the same location. - Node: the node_id where we want to perform the action. - Target node: the other node_id on the process. It is optative. If NULL, system will try to find the closest node. - Action: 5 actions can be performed:  DELETE: Node is deleted. Target node gets topology. DOWNGRADE: Node is downgraded. Target node gets topology. MOVE AND LOSE TOPOLOGY: Node is moved and lose topology. Target node gets topology. MOVE AND KEEP TOPOLOGY: Node is moved and keep topology. Target node lose topology. MOVE AND GET TOPOLOGY: Node is moved and get topology. Target node lose topology. - For moving actions, set the X and Y axis movement (in meters) where node will be displaced.' WHERE id = '3080';
